        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The global production volume is extrapolated from the US production volume based on reports from Cefic (European Chemical Industry Council), and the American Chemistry Council. According to Cefic (2016) the global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3 534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per region are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (US, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the US total sales, which amount to 518.7 billion euros out of the global 3 534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported by the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to which the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016. US production volume: According to the Environmental Protection Agency, the consumption of Sodium oxide for the year of 2015 (in USA) is estimated to be 13607771 kg. The aforementioned value is the average of the range given in the literature. Since no data were found for the global production this value was scaled accordingly. References: Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html Environmental Protection Agency, 2016, Chemical data reporting results, Available at: https://www.epa.gov/chemical-data-reporting/2016-chemical-data-reporting-results</productionVolumeComment>
