        <name xml:lang="en">sodium nitrite</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 68.995308g/mol is the molar mass of sodium nitrite (NNaO2). 61.978936g/mol is the molar mass of sodium oxide (Na2O). Sodium oxide is made by reacting sodium with sodium nitrite. It is an intermediate product in the production of sodium peroxide (Sitzmann, 2007). Chemical Reaction: 2 NaNO2 + 6 Na → 4 Na2O + N2</comment>
